---
name: Testing Rules
globs:
  - "tests/**/*.py"
---

## Framework
- Use pytest for all tests — no unittest
- Use FastAPI's TestClient for all API tests — never spin up a live server
- Use a dedicated test database that is created fresh and torn down per
  session — never touch the production database

## Structure
- Keep tests separated by layer:
  tests/test_api.py, tests/test_db.py, tests/test_integration.py
- Use pytest fixtures for all setup and teardown logic — no manual
  setup inside test functions
- Parametrize any test that runs the same logic across multiple cities
  or time windows

## Writing Tests
- Every test function name must describe the exact scenario being tested:
  test_get_spikes_returns_empty_list_when_no_data_in_window
  not test_1 or test_spikes
- Every test must have a one-line docstring explaining the scenario
- Every test must be capable of failing — no unconditional passes
- Always assert on the actual output shape, status code, and data —
  never just assert the code ran without crashing

## Test Data
- Use realistic placeholder data — real city names, plausible temperatures,
  valid timestamps — never foo, bar, or 999
- Never hardcode database URLs or credentials — read from environment
  variables or fixtures
- Do not assert on exact timestamps — use ranges or relative comparisons

## Do NOT
- Do not duplicate or overwrite developer-provided test scripts —
  extend them only
- Do not query the database directly inside API tests — go through
  the API layer only
- Do not leave commented-out tests in the codebase